### **Usage Workflow**

1. **Label Training Data:**

- Run `WorkInstructionLabeler.exe`
- Load a folder with 50-100 PowerPoint files
- Click through each file and label the text boxes using the color-coded buttons
- The visual interface shows exactly where each text box is positioned
- Click ‚ÄúSave Training Data‚Äù to export CSV
- Click ‚ÄúTrain Model‚Äù to generate `wi_extractor_model.zip`

1. **Use the Model:**

- Copy `wi_extractor_model.zip` to your `WorkInstructionExtractor` application folder
- Run your extraction - it will automatically use ML when available
- Fall back to position-based extraction if model missing or low confidence

1. **Iterate:**

- Review extraction results
- Add problem files back to the labeler
- Correct labels and retrain
- Model improves over time

### **Advantages of This Approach:**

‚úÖ **Visual feedback** - See exactly what you‚Äôre labeling in a Blend-style interface  
‚úÖ **Color-coded** - Each field type has distinct colors  
‚úÖ **Position-aware** - Shows actual text box positions from PowerPoint  
‚úÖ **Hybrid approach** - ML + position rules for best accuracy  
‚úÖ **Confidence scoring** - Know when predictions are uncertain  
‚úÖ **Iterative improvement** - Easy to add more training data  
‚úÖ **No Python dependency** - Pure .NET solution

